public class Token
extends Object
implements Comparable<Token>, Serializable

A token produced by a PostfixTokenizer during the lexing phase of processing a textual objexj pattern representation.

Token

public Token(Token.Type type,
             String filterType,
             String value)
Creates a new Token.

Parameters:
type - the Token.Type this Token will have; must not be null
filterType - the type of filter this Token is; must not be null if the supplied type is equal to Token.Type.FILTER
value - the value for this Token; may be null; must be null if the supplied Token.Type indicates that this Token does not take a value
Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if type is null, or if type.hasValue() returns false and the supplied value is non-null, or if the supplied Token.Type is not equal to Token.Type.FILTER and filterType is non-null
